result.execSummary:
The defendant Jasmine Q Watson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  


Defendant sentenced to serve 60 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 6 days time served. COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
     *   Mental Health Evaluation and take ALL prescribed
          medication, and/or any treatment deemed appropriate.          
     *   Successfully complete Anger Management.
     *   Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
          and successfully complete recommended treatment.
     *   Maintain absolute sobriety.  Defendant NOT possess or
          use any controlled substances unless by valid prescription.
     *   Successfully complete any other counseling and/or
          treatment deemed appropriate.

 Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Rights and Pretrial Incarceration Credit, received and filed

Defendant Jasmine Q Watson in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Jessica Bellows appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Defendant changes her plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Defendant Jasmine Q Watson in court with attorney Patrick Dennis Wait.  Margaret Anne Kunisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for May 17, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services "Court Reminders."    Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Davis, Branch 21.  Scheduling conference scheduled for March 18, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jasmine Q Watson in court with attorney Patrick Dennis Wait.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for October 26, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings. Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Jasmine Q Watson in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Defendant Jasmine Q Watson in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bvj  
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Judge, Branch 45.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued.  Court ordered any bail posted to be forfeited.
